'''Axel Gabriel Sj<U+00F6>str<U+00F6>m''' (16 August 1794 &ndash; 11 December 1846) was a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[poet]]. He was born in [[Janakkala]], and became professor of Greek at Helsinki in 1833. He married Margareta Sofia Helsberg in 1828. During his lifetime a few of his poems earned him a high, but short-lived, reputation in Finnish literary circles. Aside from original poetry, Sj<U+00F6>str<U+00F6>m also did translations from Greek ([[Homer]], [[Euripides]], [[Anacreon]], [[Theocritus]], and [[Johan Paulinus-Lillienstedt]]'s ''Magnus Principatus Finlandia'') and German ([[Goethe]] and Romantic poets).

==References==
* Schoolfield, George C. ''A History of Finland's Literature'', p.&nbsp;300. University of Nebraska Press, 1998. ISBN 9780803241893

